### XLVIII

### TO FORGET KNOWLEDGE

He who attends daily to learning increases in learning. He who practices
Tao daily diminishes. Again and again he humbles himself. Thus he
attains to non-doing (wu wei). He practices non-doing and yet there is
nothing left undone.

To command the empire one must not employ craft. If one uses craft he is
not fit to command the empire.

